{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They didn't get caught on the wrong foot the way the boys did in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were down to our last 50 rounds of ammunition for the guns the night that they finally got halted.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had lost one whole tank battalion, but we destroyed more German tanks than we lost.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was-- and getting the wounded out was a nightmare sometimes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the-- what we-- the way we operated, battalion aid means you're on the line.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was the surgeon of an armored combat command.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's a third of an armored division, a battalion of tanks, a battalion of armored infantry, who ride in half-tracks with machine guns and mortars, a battalion of self-propelled artillery, and then supporting troops, like engineers and medics, 3,000 men.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And each battalion had its own doctor, sometimes two for the-- and their own aid station.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They'd been set up in ruined buildings or cellars pretty close to-- 300 or 400 yards from the front line.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were getting shelled all the time, of course.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we'd have to wait until there was a break in shelling and then make a run for it with an ambulance, cram in the wounded, and then go.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had-- one of the terrifying things is when you have an aid station full of wounded men crying, groaning, and screaming, and then they start shelling it again.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The roof starts coming in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was very bloody fighting.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were up against SS troops, the 10th SS division.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We learned that they were totally criminals.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They trapped one of our aid men and killed him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I wrote about this in my book.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
